Comment:
Problem with these kinds of films? Even though they seek to shed-light on this poisonous culture? These films would be played in frats all over America and they would be cheered and revered...because ultimately? Films like THIS? Actually glorify frat life, and there are certain types of young men who want to take a bite...no matter what. These young men are not deterred, for one minute, by the 'negative' stuff. All THEY see? Is the debauchery and how much they want a piece of it.

...but perhaps worse? The fact that one day THEY will be the ones inflicting the suffering and pain onto another young man who THEY once were...but not anymore!

In fact, I'm betting that the actors in this film enjoyed every minute of it. And that speaks volumes...doesn't it?

Title: Goat Official Trailer 1 (2016) - Nick Jonas Movie
Comment: I've been thru pledging 2-times, sorority and little sister to a fraternity, and dated guys that pledged.  Now granted they aren't supposed to tell about what they did (or I did during Hell week), but this is just a bit extreme from my knowledge of being on BOTH SIDES of the pledging (member and pledge).  Some of the scenes looked pretty accurate, but there is something to say about history and the bond that is built during the entire pledge process (normally a semester, that wraps up with Hell Week where pledges must stay at the house and normally the house is locked out from any visitors that are not members or pledges. I wouldn't take back any of my experiences, and even though it was very freaking stressful at the time, I believe it made me closer to the fraternity and members. With that said, if they are doing any sexually then call it off, period!  Nobody should be forcing you to have sex, masterbate, or do anything sexually to another living being, period!  The same for forcing you to drink/eat enormous quantities of alcohol, food, water or anything else, and one should walk away if that happens as well.  The only physical thing I recall is being paddled, and that wasn't anything that I can even remember and that was 20 yrs ago!

Title: Goat Official Trailer 1 (2016) - Nick Jonas Movie
Comment: 99.9% of IFC Frats don't do anything like what this movie portrays. Yes, hazing happens but usually when the school finds out what is going on they kick the frat off campus and expel all those who participated from the university. As for NPHC fraternities I've seen and heard all sorts of things that I don't agree with... mostly branding and physical beatings. On the flip side Iv'e seen the positive impacts fraternities and sororities have on a community. I've seen many GLO raise hundreds of thousands for charities and actually work with many local business's that struggle to stay afloat. I've actually seen a family that lost everything they own from a fire a week before Christmas and a fraternity actually assisted by donating food, clothes, and buying the kids better Christmas gifts than they would have received had their house not burned, then the frat partnered with habitat of humanity and helped build the family a new home. But you wont see Hollywood make a movie about that...
